  "correctAnswer": "2",
  "section": "Math",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Set the function equal to 4",
      "content": "The function is $f(x)=\\frac{10}{7}x+\\frac{8}{7}$. The condition $f(x)=4$ gives:<br/>$$4=\\frac{10}{7}x+\\frac{8}{7}$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Clear the denominators",
      "content": "Multiply both sides by $7$:<br/>$$28=10x+8$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Solve for x",
      "content": "Subtract $8$, then divide by $10$:<br/>$$20=10x$$<br/>$$x=2$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Check",
      "content": "Substitute $x=2$: $\\frac{10}{7}(2)+\\frac{8}{7}=\\frac{20}{7}+\\frac{8}{7}=\\frac{28}{7}=4$. This confirms the output is exactly $4$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Answer",
      "content": "The value of $x$ is <strong>2</strong>."
    }
  ]
}